#compdef turbowatch
# =============================================================================
# turbowatch — Gajus Kuizinas's "Extremely fast file change
#              detector and task orchestrator for Node.js" — a
#              CLI for watching file trees + orchestrating
#              dependent tasks via user-defined TypeScript
#              configuration scripts.  Distinguishing from
#              `nodemon`, `chokidar-cli`, `entr`, `watchexec`,
#              `chokidar` directly, and Webpack-style watchers
#              by:
#                - TYPESCRIPT-CONFIG-DRIVEN: every turbowatch
#                  invocation loads a `turbowatch.ts` script
#                  (loadable via jiti for inline TS), which
#                  exports a Watcher configuration object
#                  with subscriptions + onChange handlers
#                - SUBSCRIPTION MODEL: configure named
#                  subscriptions with expressions (allOf /
#                  anyOf / dirname / glob / suffix /
#                  ...) — match-engine inspired by Facebook
#                  Watchman
#                - TASK ORCHESTRATION: each subscription's
#                  onChange handler can spawn shell commands
#                  via zx (Google's shell-scripting library),
#                  with built-in process tree kill on
#                  re-trigger
#                - WATCHMAN-INSPIRED but pure-Node: uses
#                  chokidar (FSWatcher) instead of Watchman
#                  daemon, with optional Watchman backend
#                - ABORT CONTROLLER + GRACEFUL SHUTDOWN: SIGINT/
#                  SIGTERM propagate through abort signal +
#                  pidtree to all child processes
#                - GLOB-EXPANDED CONFIG PATHS: invoke with
#                  multiple `turbowatch.ts` paths or glob
#                  patterns (`**/turbowatch.ts`)
#                - ROARR-NATIVE LOGGING: logs are JSON-line
#                  structured via Roarr; opt-in via ROARR_LOG=
#                  true env var; pretty-print via @roarr/cli
#              Used by monorepo developers, Node.js library
#              maintainers, and TypeScript build pipelines
#              needing a turn-key file-watching + task-running
#              orchestrator with structured logging.
#
# Author:  Gajus Kuizinas (gajus on GitHub) — author + sole
#          maintainer of turbowatch.  Also author of the
#          headline library Roarr, Slonik (PostgreSQL client),
#          global-agent (HTTP proxy agent), fastify-webpack-hot,
#          and other 100+ Node.js / TypeScript libraries.
# Source:  https://github.com/gajus/turbowatch
#          https://github.com/gajus/turbowatch/blob/master/src/bin/turbowatch.ts
#          https://github.com/gajus/turbowatch/blob/master/src/Logger.ts
# CLI:     src/bin/turbowatch.ts — `yargs(hideBin(process.argv))
#          .command('$0 [patterns...]', ...)`.  Headline
#          library: Roarr (Gajus's own JSON-line structured
#          logger for Node.js + browsers); turbowatch uses
#          `Roarr.child({ package: 'turbowatch' })` from
#          Logger.ts as its sole logging surface, gated by
#          ROARR_LOG environment variable.
# Library: roarr ("Roarr" — Gajus Kuizinas — released 2017 as a
#          JSON-line structured logger for Node.js + browsers,
#          designed for DISTRIBUTED SYSTEMS where logs are
#          piped to external aggregators rather than processed
#          in-process.  Distinct from Winston (transports +
#          formatters), Bunyan (Joyent JSON), Pino (high-perf
#          JSON), Consola (UnJS pretty + browser), and Debug
#          (namespace-only).  Roarr's central feature: a
#          MINIMAL JSON-LINE FORMAT with `.child({ context })`
#          inheritance, GLOBAL ROARR object for browser/Node
#          unified API, ASYNC LOCAL STORAGE integration for
#          per-request context propagation, and DESIGN PHIL-
#          OSOPHY of "log first, transport second" — Roarr
#          emits JSON to stdout/stderr and EXPECTS users to
#          pipe to @roarr/cli or external aggregators for
#          pretty-printing/filtering/forwarding.)
# License: BSD-3-Clause (turbowatch); BSD-3-Clause (roarr)
# Status:  turbowatch — 971+ stars on gajus/turbowatch, used
#          by TypeScript monorepos + library build pipelines;
#          Roarr — 856+ stars on gajus/roarr, ~15M weekly npm
#          downloads, foundational dependency of Slonik
#          ecosystem + InvokeAI frontend + Xcraft-Inc/global-
#          agent + nodeexx/code-snippet-sharing + knot-dots
#          + sebinsua/modern-node-app + 1000+ Node.js services.
#
